reg_info.full_title: O. Reg. 17/02: SOCIAL HOUSING SERVICES CORPORATION

content.content: 1. In this Regulation,  “corporation” means Social Housing Services Corporation established under section 140 of the Act. O. Reg. 17/02, s. 1.
content.raw_html:
1. In this Regulation,

“corporation” means Social Housing Services Corporation established under section 140 of the Act. O. Reg. 17/02, s. 1.

content.section: Members of the corporation — prescribed housing providers
content.content: 2. (1) The housing providers that are non-profit housing corporations listed in Schedule 1 are prescribed as members of the corporation under clause 140 (2) (c) of the Act. O. Reg. 17/02, s. 2 (1). (2) The housing providers that are non-profit housing co-operatives listed in Schedule 2 are prescribed as members of the corporation under clause 140 (2) (d) of the Act. O. Reg. 17/02, s. 2 (2).
content.raw_html:
2. (1) The housing providers that are non-profit housing corporations listed in Schedule 1 are prescribed as members of the corporation under clause 140 (2) (c) of the Act. O. Reg. 17/02, s. 2 (1).

(2) The housing providers that are non-profit housing co-operatives listed in Schedule 2 are prescribed as members of the corporation under clause 140 (2) (d) of the Act. O. Reg. 17/02, s. 2 (2).

content.section: Members of the corporation — other housing providers
content.content: 3. (1) A housing provider that provides housing under a program listed in Schedule 4 and whose membership application is approved by the board of directors of the corporation becomes a member of the corporation, as provided by clause 140 (2) (e) of the Act. O. Reg. 17/02, s. 3 (1). (2) A housing provider described in subsection (1) becomes a member of the corporation on the first day of the month after the month in which the board of directors of the corporation approves the application. O. Reg. 17/02, s. 3 (2).
content.raw_html:
3. (1) A housing provider that provides housing under a program listed in Schedule 4 and whose membership application is approved by the board of directors of the corporation becomes a member of the corporation, as provided by clause 140 (2) (e) of the Act. O. Reg. 17/02, s. 3 (1).

(2) A housing provider described in subsection (1) becomes a member of the corporation on the first day of the month after the month in which the board of directors of the corporation approves the application. O. Reg. 17/02, s. 3 (2).

content.section: Objects of the corporation — prescribed housing providers and programs
content.content: 4. (1) The housing providers listed in Schedules 1 and 3 and the housing providers that are members of the corporation pursuant to section 3 are prescribed as housing providers for the purposes of clauses 141 (a), (b), (c) and (d) of the Act. O. Reg. 150/03, s. 1. (1.1) The housing providers listed in Schedule 2 are prescribed housing providers for the purposes of clauses 141 (b), (c) and (d) of the Act. O. Reg. 150/03, s. 1. (2) The housing programs listed in Schedule 4 are prescribed as housing programs for the purposes of clauses 141 (a) and (c) of the Act. O. Reg. 17/02, s. 4 (2).
content.raw_html:
4. (1) The housing providers listed in Schedules 1 and 3 and the housing providers that are members of the corporation pursuant to section 3 are prescribed as housing providers for the purposes of clauses 141 (a), (b), (c) and (d) of the Act. O. Reg. 150/03, s. 1.

(1.1) The housing providers listed in Schedule 2 are prescribed housing providers for the purposes of clauses 141 (b), (c) and (d) of the Act. O. Reg. 150/03, s. 1.

(2) The housing programs listed in Schedule 4 are prescribed as housing programs for the purposes of clauses 141 (a) and (c) of the Act. O. Reg. 17/02, s. 4 (2).

content.section: Powers of the corporation’s board — prescribed housing providers
content.content:
5. (1) The housing providers listed in Schedules 1 and 3 and the housing providers that are members of the corporation pursuant to section 3 are prescribed as housing providers for the purposes of clauses 142 (1) (b), (d), (e) and (f) of the Act. O. Reg. 150/03, s. 2. (1.1) The housing providers listed in Schedule 2 are prescribed as housing providers for the purposes of clauses 142 (1) (b), (e) and (f) of the Act. O. Reg. 150/03, s. 2. (2) Those housing providers listed in Schedule 1 or 2 that are required by regulation to meet the provincial requirements under clause 93 (2) (f) of the Act are prescribed as housing providers for the purposes of clause 142 (1) (c) of the Act.
